and I could still get paid that would be great.   Schools continue to get worse since the end of WWII when it was decided that the feds should help 'impacted' school districts with money for the extra kids in their systems because of military posts or related industry.  People are really good at maximizing what you pay them for...  If you pay them for the kids that are occupying desks they will become better babysitters.  If you pay them for the kids actually learning and advancing (along with performance responsibilities for the teachers) they will become better educators (without additional money and without minimizing the class size)...   We used the public schools to process our kids so that they would know how to interface with their peers.  We never relied on the public schools to educate our kids as we did it at home AND structured our family vacations to expose our kids to Art, Science, Museums, old empty prison tours, etc...   Both of my kids have thanked their Mother and me for preparing them to compete successfully (YES SUCCESSFULLY) with their peers. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1386" language="en" documentId="2686" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Dave" date="Aug 29, 2013 8:28PM" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://living.msn.com/family-parenting/the-family-room-blog-post?post=ab228ffc-1e99-4b37-a7b8-0b6a4c3fb240" topic="public-private-schools" thumbsUp="5" thumbsDown="0" origId="2686" notes="" title="Is it wrong to send kids to private school?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1386"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>